external_knowledge:
- "crossed the horizon" refers to the latest available market data;
- "celestial bodies" here metaphorically represent the exchanges;
- "day" refers to the date of the market data;
- "starlight" metaphorically represents the closing price of the financial instruments.

sql:
SELECT t.trader_name, ts.action
FROM traders t
JOIN trading_sessions ts ON t.trader_id = ts.trader_id;

SELECT instrument_name, instrument_type
FROM financial_instruments
ORDER BY instrument_name ASC;

SELECT SUM(session_profit_loss) AS total_profit_loss
FROM trading_sessions
WHERE trader_id = 1;

SELECT data_id 
FROM market_data
WHERE instrument_id = 5000 AND open_price > close_price;
